 as \"une carotte\". Nicely expressive, don't you think?\nFranglais always goes most wrong when the words are almost the same but the meanings are different. \"Forager\" is another: to drill (e.g. for oil or gas).\nI like the idea of foraging for oil or gas. Sounds much more back-to-nature!", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "115355531", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115365551", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1525276524000}, "author": "dave6723", "author_id": "18522661", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Pro tip:\nIf you're determined to be a pedant, have a look on Google or Wiki first. Might save you making a fool of yourself next time.", "recommendation_count": "6", "in_reply_to": "115351142", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115362274", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1525272234000}, "author": "Jon Davies", "author_id": "12894240", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "What's in a name? Yours seems to indicate a relationship with emotion. Coincidence?", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "115334298", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115357147", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1525265173000}, "author": "SarahPalin", "author_id": "3342276", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Provide link please.I think you are talking rubbish", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "115335990", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115355761", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1525263711000}, "author": "Steve__M", "author_id": "18247935", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "It's a bit vague:\nBQSTART\nOur analysis does not cover potential CO2 that is emitted during mining, grinding, and spreading of rock powder, which leads to a CO2 penalty, decreasing the overall net CO2 sequestration. Given the fact that EW would only become economic at carbon prices above 60\u2009$\u2009t\u2009CO2\u22121, it seems highly unlikely that it would be used with carbon-intensive energy production [38]. If electricity w