rain cause the train to be derailed and the loss of many lives.\nBut to say because this catastrophic incident is possible does not mean driving rapidly and dangerously is the only outcome- the least damaging outcome if you do it frequently is that you will be caught and lose your driving license - which could be catastrophic for you.\nHence so many variable outcomes means that science does not use the term catastrophic for AGW.\nAs for proxies- all temperature readings are proxies- mercury thermometers use expansion of the metal - laser or infrared thermometers use a proxy- this is measuring the black body radiation.Likewise certain plants grow in a defined temperature range- so if their pollen is found with datable material that gives avery accurate picture of the temperature range over 100s or 1000s of years.", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "115601605", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "you were on an empty highway", "effect": "have no ill effect- simply arriving safely at your destination"}, {"cause": null, "effect": "loss of your home and a divorce"}, {"cause": "you", "effect": "an injury that prevented you from working"}, {"cause": null, "effect": "a major road incident that killed others"}, {"cause": "this catastrophic incident is possible", "effect": "to say"}]}, {"id": "115614454", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1525876403000}, "author": "JulesBywaterLees", "author_id": "4738374", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "The problem has been around longer than the existence of the internet and described better-\nBQSTART\n\u201cThere is a cult of ignorance in the United States, and there has always been. The strain of anti-intellectualism has been a constant thread winding its way through our political and cultural life, nurtured by the false notion that democracy means that 'my ignorance is just as good as your knowledge.\u201d \n\u2015 Isaac Asimov\nBQEND back in 1984.\nBut of course he is just one of many who have been dismayed at ant