 you are not diminishing the importance of CO2 in the least - you are in fact merely highlighting just how sensitive the climate is to CO2.", "recommendation_count": "12", "in_reply_to": "116012029", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "any excess water vapour simply precipitates and quickly falls back to earth", "effect": "water vapour can not drive climate change"}, {"cause": "something else", "effect": "the temperature to rise first"}]}, {"id": "116023606", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526822007000}, "author": "Vlamingo", "author_id": "15902664", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I am not disputing your right to say what you like here, Bob - merely pointing out that if we wish to properly inform ourselves, we must take care to go to the most reliable sources.\nThere's really no way around this.", "recommendation_count": "11", "in_reply_to": "116011495", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116023351", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526821532000}, "author": "Walsunda", "author_id": "12483673", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"That\" (public roads, public transport, public schools, and public hospitals are good because they benefit the community as do renewable energy sources and also attract a subsidy) \"is a false comparison that does not justify subsidies to renewables.\"\nWhy is it a false comparison?", "recommendation_count": "11", "in_reply_to": "116008238", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "they benefit the community as do renewable energy sources and also attract a subsidy", "effect": "that roads are good"}]}, {"id": "116023099", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526820978000}, "author": "Walsunda", "author_id": "12483673", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I asked you \"What underlying assumptions are there in science\" and you said in reply \"every hypothesis about the climate has lots of assumptions about what will happen that cannot be properly falsified by the scientific method\".\nIf an hypothesis has assump