ttee of my local creek revegetation group. We run a nursery to grow plants endemic to the catchment which we supply to members involved up and down the creeks. We were also auspicing three other groups involved in organic vegetables and indigenous food plants. \nIn the lead up to the 2015 Queensland state election in which Premier Newman lost his seat and government, we had an interesting experience with a local men's shed group. They had already shared space with another group in the electorate but were keen to move elsewhere.\nOur nursery adjoined and shared expertise with a Greening Australia nursery, the operators of which were told with days to spare that their operation was winding up. Their parent organisation removed almost all their stock within days. We took what we could salvage from the skip and organised ameeting of Brisbane revegetation groups at short notice. \nAlmost immediately our local LNP councillor told us the men's shed group would be moving in. They came and had a look and told us they'd be taking over.\nAt the meeting we decided to support the very skilled staff in continuing the native nursery which dealt with plants beyond our catchment selling them to the public. We told the council we couldn't operate without that valuable synergy. The councillor was not happy at the time.\nThe groups we auspiced at the other location said they were happy to share with the men's shed group and the council realised they had a location for the men's shed group to build their shed, already paid for by the Newman government, at that site.\nWe auspiced the new nursery while our other auspiced groups became independent. Within a year that nursery was up and running and paying its permanent staff. The men's shed group built their shed and, except for one unfortunate incident where their president told an indigenous woman to move on, have more or less fitted in. That president has pulled out for health reasons and their operation seems to be running more smoothly.\nA few months after that meeting to organise to keep the native plant nursery running as a worker run enterprise, my daughter defeated Newman at the state election. With every election there's always a bit of a flurry from the tories but that one was bigger than most.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "115945838", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115949669", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526630034000}, "author": "Friarbird", "author_id": "12641156", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Yet none of that constitutes a credible case.All you've done is make hollow accusations.Based on a familiar conservative formula;\n\"All the things I deplore are caused by people I never liked anyway.\"", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "115949343", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "people", "effect": "all the things i deplore"}]}, {"id": "115949468", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526629612000}, "author": "BertFromEltham", "author_id": "14126678", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "They are fighting over deck chairs on the Titanic.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "115947441", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115949459", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526629599000}, "author": "Friarbird", "author_id": "12641156", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"...one of the very few members of this government who can write his own name and speak in sentences.\"You did it AGAIN !I laughed out loud.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "115949101", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115949343", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526629355000}, "author": "Michael123456", "author_id": "16875522", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "An earlier comment from another questioned why parts of the press focus on Aust\u2019s supposedly poor record with climate change mitigation measures.\nAt the time I thought that focus was due to (1) genuine concern and (2) politics, with the coming election (next 