utable - but I think that makes all the more important that we accept the science as it is presented to us without any of the exaggeration or undue emphasis that, no matter how well intended, a number of people wish to apply to it.\nIf we exaggerate or are overly dogmatic then we give a handle for the AGW contrarians to pull on and cry foul. \nIf you'll forgive me for repeating myself from above, I submit that if you're going to tell someone where they are wrong then you have to accept the bit/s where they are right and work from there.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "116532551", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "human activity", "effect": "the warming we observe"}]}, {"id": "116520841", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527952357000}, "author": "bassireland", "author_id": "2849622", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nThe sea ice loss in the Arctic continues it's seasonal decline and at the moment is being shown by NSIDC in one set of graphics (Charctic) at the second lowest level for May\nBQEND\nSecond-lowest? So you admit there\u2019s a recovery in progress?", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "116519424", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116520740", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527952111000}, "author": "ComfortablyPlumb", "author_id": "14842422", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "sorry for typos - small screen, bright sun, big fingers.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "116520360", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116532612", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527981070000}, "author": "bassireland", "author_id": "2849622", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Indeed. When we stand on the shoulders of giants it is the consensus that forms the platform", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "116524665", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116520585", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527951764000}, "author": "ComfortablyPlumb", "author_id": "14842422", "schema_org_type": "http://