e remaining people continued to produce pollution at the same per capita rate. Would anyone say: \"Pollution is just as bad as it ever was because each individual continues to produce the same amount of pollution as they did before the epidemic.\"? Actually, pollution would be half as bad as before because each unit of land area is producing half a much pollution as before - even if every individual was still producing the same amount of pollution as before. Suppose some country doubled its population; but each individual in that country now only produces half the pollution that they individually did before. Would anyone say: \"Pollution is much less of a problem now because each individual is producing half the pollution - even though the total amount of pollution being produced is unchanged.\"? It is the amount of pollution that a country produces for each unit of its land area that is key - regardless of how many citizens are involved in the production of that pollution.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "115822557", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "each individual continues to produce the same amount of pollution as they did before the epidemic", "effect": "as it ever was"}, {"cause": "each unit of land area is producing half a much pollution as before even if every individual was still producing the same amount of pollution as before", "effect": "actually pollution would be half as bad as before"}, {"cause": "each individual is producing half the pollution", "effect": "pollution is much less of a problem now even though the total amount of pollution being produced is unchanged"}]}, {"id": "115823180", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526358437000}, "author": "RhondaMay", "author_id": "12229833", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "No - just aware ...", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "115821428", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115823179", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526358427000}, "author": "Crankydaks", "author_id": "168183