ate studies could not either. \nBut science can know that there are some serious issues with this issue - and with the balmy 3 degree warmer planet they promise us by on purpose mixing up the feedback sensitivity of 2xCO2 with some idea that it can not be more than 3 degrees whatever we do as their private sensitivity (or giving carbon-only sensitivity). \nI have said this before, science is running after the pace of change. \nThe nation of USA like that since Trump canceled the NASA's Carbon Monitoring System (CMS)\nhttp://www.sciencemag.org/news/2018/05/trump-white-house-quietly-cancels-nasa-research-verifying-greenhouse-gas-cuts\nIt saved the US a NASA post costing 10 million dollars a year. Because there is much more profit to be made in pretending one move change way faster than science can keep up with. \nI bet it will be popular to chose \"harakiri\" well in advance of having to see own grandchildren in eyes and explain.", "recommendation_count": "10", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "that", "effect": "small changes to how much at which latitudes and seasons"}, {"cause": "our big planets tugging on our orbit", "effect": null}, {"cause": "also the plio pleistocene also changed own harmonics internally on our planet around a million years ago", "effect": "and that is not enough"}]}, {"id": "115700747", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526066493000}, "author": "DennisHorne", "author_id": "4446531", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I've seen various numbers but this site reckons 90% fresh water on the surface is held in the Antarctic ice sheet:https://www.sciencedaily.com/terms/antarctic_ice_sheet.htm", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "115691535", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115696227", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526057133000}, "author": "Erik Frederiksen", "author_id": "15131989", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Thanks for the link. I\u2019ve been curious to see what more research would turn up. Even witho