ently alters forest fuels characteristics across multiple time horizons.\nhttp://rstb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/371/1696/2015017\nBQEND", "recommendation_count": "19", "in_reply_to": "116001280", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116001280", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526758290000}, "author": "JimKerr", "author_id": "16721037", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "What I state is fact. Wildfires, mudslides, \"drought\" in CA are not brought on by AGW.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "115976718", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115935643", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526576811000}, "author": "ID2310987", "author_id": "2515806", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "So \"it appears\" doesn't mean quite likely in your world? Especially given that scientists don't tend to use language that suggests something is 100% sure. And what makes it you being disingenuous and not me is that nowhere did I say that what the scientist said either proves or disproves that wildfires were greater in the 20s/30s. It was Guy who said \"and wildfires in particular are well below the levels in the early part of the last century.\" And yet you chose to pick a quarrel with me. Funny that!And it was you who is still trying to make out that wildfires were greater then i.e. \"My point by tossing at 60% was only to show that even if it were that much, that wildfire acreage would STILL be more than current levels.\" with no data given to back it up. Even funnier.", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "115935080", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115935559", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526576671000}, "author": "Bernie Thomas", "author_id": "17746707", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"Believe it or not I ask these questions in the spirit of genuine enquiry as I'm utterly baffled by this stance and wish to understand\"\nMy point had to do with the selection of a four year old chart to show as the lede to th