 (and downloaded) from NOAA's \"Climate at a Glance\" webpage.\nSelect the \"Statewide -> Time Series\" tabs (direct link), then set up the parameters as follows (noting that the \"water year\" in the US is from October to September, and also that there are 4 \"Drought Index\" options under the \"Parameter\" menu)\nBQSTART\nParameter -> Precipitation Time Scale -> 12-Month  Month -> September (!) Start Year -> 1895 End Year -> 2017 State -> California\nBQEND\nthen hit the \"Plot\" button.\nUsing a spreadsheet to plot that data (from 1970) gives me a graph that is almost identical to Governor Brown's ... except for 2014 !\nThe last 6 years of data (in inches) I downloaded from NOAA are :2012 : 16.44 (just above 15\" in the above photo)2013 : 16.95 (slightly higher than 2012 ...)2014 : 12.39 (instead of ~5\" !?!)2015 : 16.792016 : 22.722017 : 34.54 (= Dana's \"followed immediately by its wettest year on record\")\nNote that the \"spike\" in the photo above in 1983 was to just over 40\".\nMy downloaded data includes :1941 : 34.871983 : 40.411998 : 37.65\nFor me, 40.41 > 34.54, but what would I know ?", "recommendation_count": "8", "in_reply_to": "115801192", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115830495", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526376826000}, "author": "ID2310987", "author_id": "2515806", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Guy, you posted that once already and I posted this link which includes a discussion of that graph and a quote from an expert in the field who looked into it and concluded it was comparing \"apples with oranges\" https://andthentheresphysics.wordpress.com/2015/10/30/the-mysterious-wildfire-chart/#commentsYou can also see in the comments below links to studies that suggest western USA wildfires are increasing.", "recommendation_count": "23", "in_reply_to": "115828497", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115828497", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1526374365000}, "author": "GuyWarren", "author_id": "13408113", "schema_org_type": "http://