nd unmanned weather stations. It was presented to the European Geosciences Union in Vienna in April. The Antarctic has the highest elevation of any continent, and consequently fierce f\u00f6hn winds. The new results show that these hot winds are making a significant contribution to ice melt.\n\n\n\n\n", "keyword_urls": ["https://www.theguardian.com/environment/climate-change", "https://www.theguardian.com/world/natural-disasters", "https://www.theguardian.com/tone/features"], "share_count": "0", "description": "Recent research on the rate of Antarctic ice melt points to the effect of warm f\u00f6hn winds", "date_published": {"$date": 1525465832000}, "date_modified": {"$date": 1525467623000}, "authors": ["David Hambling"], "article_section": "World news", "article_tags": ["Antarctica", "Climate change", "Natural disasters and extreme weather"], "og_fields": {"og:url": "http://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/04/weatherwatch-why-does-antarctic-ice-melt-in-the-depths-of-winter", "og:description": "Recent research on the rate of Antarctic ice melt points to the effect of warm f\u00f6hn winds", "og:image": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c34cb4553a7ba819bab430251f8bd8f240afbb56/58_64_1942_1165/master/1942.jpg?width=1200&height=630&quality=85&auto=format&fit=crop&overlay-align=bottom%2Cleft&overlay-width=100p&overlay-base64=L2ltZy9zdGF0aWMvb3ZlcmxheXMvdGctZGVmYXVsdC5wbmc&s=e44fff938f30c910ea2492d8727b7942", "og:type": "article", "og:title": "Weatherwatch: \u200bwhy does Antarctic ice melt in the depths of winter?"}, "discussion_section_open": false, "headline": "\u200b", "article_image": [{"type": "http://schema.org/ImageObject", "properties": {"representativeOfPage": "true", "url": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c34cb4553a7ba819bab430251f8bd8f240afbb56/58_64_1942_1165/master/1942.jpg?width=700&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=b124aa948ffb7de46ab11590e9af93ed", "width": "1942", "height": "1165", "contentUrl": "https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c34cb4553a7ba819bab430251f8b