 CO2 and the need for CCS.\nHowever the point I make is that oil is quickly becoming energy intense as well.On a grid level other forms of storage make sense- like pumped, batteries are great in domestic, business, and transport use, just as laptops are very useful. And it is a challenge- but I'm optimistic.\nIf we can't fix the short fall and then reliant on the nuclear industry then I'm less so because the track record recently has been poor on delivery.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "116224218", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "the processing and extraction inputs", "effect": "however oil requires energy to extract and process so saudi oil is lower in co2 content because it requires less energy to extract and process canadian tarsands is 25 % more co2"}, {"cause": "it requires less energy to extract and process", "effect": "so saudi oil is lower in co2 content"}, {"cause": "the track record recently has been poor on delivery", "effect": "if we ca n't fix the short fall and then reliant on the nuclear industry then i 'm less so"}]}, {"id": "116225828", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527259925000}, "author": "onthefence", "author_id": "2490315", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nJulesBywaterLees - If I point out that a tweet is not the normal way to communicate complex arguments or policy I am not trolling.\nBQEND\nJules, most scientific organisations use twitter to link to their latest research and latest results. Twitter is used to communicate.It isn't a bad thing for a professional science communicator to communicate on Twitter.\nYou've now decided to start arguing about Twitter.Unstoppable.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "116224700", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "116283232", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1527410730000}, "author": "Mazter", "author_id": "11150889", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nThe main joy of these threads is watching a tiny cult of scientific illiterates